metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #106
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License

metadata.name: Paper Planes #71
metadata.description:
The joys of childhood are too easily forgotten. Paper Planes is a generative art collection celebrating the joy and magic of origami: from the simplest materials spring delightful forms brimming with ingenuity.

In homage to the handicraft of paper folding, we developed a collection of four pens each with a unique hand-drawn feel: Ink, Pencil, Gel and Dip. They ensure each of our ten origami birds are sketched with subtle imperfections.

Many of the birds are folded from patterned paper based on three traditional Japanese patterns: Seigaiha, K≈çjitsunagi and Shipp≈ç. Other birds are crafted from block coloured paper which provides pop and contrast whilst sometimes birds match their background, accentuating the hand-drawn strokes that sketched them.

A range of layouts bring each mint to life. Birds can flock and fly across the page. They can be confined to a regimented grid or they can escape and embrace the chaos of the currents. Contrasting frames and borders highlight different colours within each of the 15 handcrafted palettes.

If you're feeling mischievous you can press 'C' in live view to ruffle some feathers‚Ä¶

https://www.phaust.art/paper-planes

----------

In live view, press 'S' to save a high resolution download or add '&size=#' to the end of the URL to render at a custom height.

Original artwork by Phaust. Spring 2022. London / Brighton. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Chord Unknown #51
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Seriscope Painting (2) #71
metadata.description:
Seriscope Paintings are composed via a generative printing process similar to serigraphy (silkscreen). A number of abstract paintings were produced traditionally using a paper marbling technique and used as a dataset to combine 4 single-colour halftone layers to make the image.

Seriscope paintings are generatively composed from a selection of:

40 Background (Who) Paintings
61 Midground (What) Paintings
61 Midground (Where) Paintings
81 Foreground (Why) Paintings

The title of each painting is also generatively composed at the time of mint within the attributes of the work - who, what, where and why.

Ryan Thompson, Jan 2022
@RT_Artwork
